  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOMG Improved Cookstoves in Burundi - A Cleaner Climate Initiative (Dukingire - Igiti)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Isle of Man Government (IOMG) International Development - Small Grant funding for 2021-23. The project will improve access to sustainable cooking methods by stimulating the production, purchase, and use of an additional 13,500 improved cleaner energy cook-stoves and to catalyse conditions for sustainable cook-stove market development in Ngozi province, Burundi.

IOMG will provide grant funding of GBP 100,000 and the remaining co-funding is intended to be raised via fundraising in Isle of Man</narrative>
  </description>
